archivesspace-development.title: investigate best way to handle orphaned bioghists

comments.body:
This adds complexity to the workflow in #64.

The idea of that workflow is to import any bioghist notes that can be robustly associated with name entities into the corresponding Agent records, and delete all bioghist notes from the EAD. This is predicated on the logic that bioghist notes are usually associated with a name (since they make little sense otherwise). 

Exempting orphaned biographical notes implies an inverse query that extracts notes that cannot robustly be associated with a name.

| Certificate Program  | Last Year Updated |

The following ensured that 6 Items which had not been mapped to the "Creative Writing Program, 1995-2020" certificate program Collection are mapped:

```
cert_collection = DSpace::CLI::SeniorThesisCollection.find_for_handle('88435/dsp01gx41mh91n')

query = DSpace::CLI::SeniorThesisCommunity.find_by_class_year('2020')
sub_query = query.find_by_certificate_program('Creative Writing Program')

unmapped = sub_query.results.select { |i| i.collections.select { |c| c.title.include?('Creative Writing Program') }.empty? }
unmapped.map { |i| cert_collection.add_item(i); cert_collection.update }
cert_collection.index
```

pulfalight.title: Request Cart should scale for Mobile
"Add to Cart" should only appear on leaf node show pages.
"Add to Cart" should not display if an item is already in the cart

comments.body: Sorry, as I think about this more, perhaps we should allow the user to remove the item with a button if it's already in the cart? "Remove Item from Cart" with the appropriate icon might be preferable to just the text "item added to cart". The language should be  consistent with the AddToCart button. I think it currently uses container label (i.e., "box") instead of "item"?

@tpendragon a few thoughts: 

- Can you provide a list of the scenarios you are testing for, along with the fixtures and component ids that represent them? I'm having trouble finding components to test with in the subset of data we load.
- One should not be able to add an entire series to the cart, but should instead be able to select from a pick-list of child components.
- The cart detail should not scale in width based on the viewport size. On a mobile device, it should take up the entire screen.
- Somehow the icons look different in the header CartToggle component and the CartDetail and AddToCart components. 
- The AddToCart button should be visibly disabled or replaced with "Item added to cart" text if the item has already been added to the cart.
- The "Located In" field only lists subcontainers, but it should also list the container. I'm also curious how the container gets passed to Aeon as I don't see it when I inspect the form that gets posted to Aeon. When requesting C1588_c4, Folder 2 is listed as both the container and subcontainer in Aeon.
- The title in the CartDetail component should be the full title. It seems to cut off the dates that would distinguish it from other items. (Looking at C1588_c4 for reference.)
@sdellis Sorry, I've been using ASpace records. We haven't nailed down fixtures from ASpace yet.

@sdellis I created https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/issues/440, https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/issues/441, and https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/issues/442 as follow ups so we can handle those things in parallel and smaller chunks after this is merged. Seem okay?
@tpendragon I agree, it's good to move those into separate tickets. Commented on one after thinking more about it.
@sdellis @eliotjordan I think these are both taken care of.

requests.title: Converting Help Me Get it to use Illiad API instead of open url
AEON items should never show help me get it in the form

comments.body: @carolyncole I will confirm with SC staff that don't want any contextual behavior by type of user on the Aeon items. In normal times 50% of their users don't have PU accounts.

AEON requests do not force a login during the request process, so we do not have accurate information about the user.   When they are already logged in the form works.  When the have not yet logged in the form does not work.  We should ignore the user for AEON.
